<A NAME="q1"></A><H2>What is GuidMagic?</H2>
<P>
<B>GuildMagic.com</B> is a system for helping Everquest players and their guild masters to keep useful and accurate lists of their guild members, their levels and their skills.
<P>
<B>Guild leaders</B> will love GuildMagic because they no longer need to make endless changes to their guild roster to keep it up to date. Guild members are responsible for keeping their own character details up to date.
<P>
<B>Guild members</B> will love GuildMagic because managing your characters is easy and GuildMagic allows you to <B>find other characters</B> on your server with a similar level, race, class or timezone. You can even use GuildMagic to find players on your server with <B>trade skills</B> you need!
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q2"></A><H2>Who wrote GuildMagic and why?</H2>
<P>
GuildMagic was written by an enthusiastic EverQuest player (<A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=11"><B>Lusanne</B></A>) that wanted a way to help out her guild. Lusanne works for a <B>british web design company</B> <A HREF="http://www.otn.co.uk/">On The Net</A> that specialises in developing database driven and <B>e-commerce</B> enabled web sites.
<P>
Guildmagic runs on On The Net's own Windows 2000 based web server and is written using <B>Cold Fusion</B> 4.5.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q3"></A><H2>Who's the woman in the picture on the left?</H2>
<P>
That's <A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=11">Lusanne</A> at level 48 stood in The Overthere watching one of Norrath's spectacular sunsets. Lusanne is an <B>Enchantress</B> and is usually in human form. In that picture she's wearing her Crystalline Robes and has put her steins away.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q4"></A><H2>Why do I need to create a user?</H2>
<P>
Most EverQuest players have <B>more than one character</B>. In order to give you a single login and password that allows control over all your Everquest characters we needed to create a user and password system.
<P>
Once you have created your user you can make as many characters as you like. Your characters can be on <B>any server</B> and in <B>any guild</B>. Even if you have more than one Everquest account you only need one GuildMagic user.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q5"></A><H2>Are you going to sell my email address to advertisers?</H2>
<P>
<B>Absolutely not</B>. Your email address is only required in case you forget your username or password. We have no plans to sell your email address to advertisers. <B>We hate spam.</B> We know how annoying unsolicited email is. We would not subject our users to more of it.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q5a"></A><H2>Who will be able to see my email address?</H2>
<P>
You can put an email address on your user and on each character you create under your user. The email address you put on your user will only be visible to your guild leader. The email address you put on your character is visible to anyone.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q5b"></A><H2>What if I don't want everyone to see everything about my EverQuest character?</H2>
<P>
You can mark your characters as anonymous, just like in EverQuest. Click <B>edit</B> next to your character on the my user page. On the edit character page there is a tickbox called <B>Character Anonymous</B>. Tick that and click <B>Update Character</B>. Your character information will now only be visible to your guild mates.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q6"></A><H2>Are you trying to steal my EQ account?</H2>
<P>
<B>No way!</B> In fact when you create your user you are expressly requested NOT to use your EverQuest account name and password. <B>This service is not run by Verant.</B> We will never need to know you Everquest account name or password for any reason. Do not under any circumstances give those details to us or anyone claiming to be related to GuildMagic.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q7"></A><H2>Are versions of GuildMagic planned for Ultima Online/Asheron's Call/Shadowbane/etc?</H2>
<P>
Quite <B>possibly</B>. That will depend on how successful the EverQuest version of GuildMagic is. The system has been designed to be able to cope with whatever new games come along. While GuildMagic is still new I expect to spend <B>more time tweaking</B> the EverQuest version than producing a whole new version for a different game but if you're really keen to see a version for your own game then please <A HREF="mailto:lus@otn.co.uk">email me</A> to let me know. I'll use the number of requests I get to decide which game to develop for next.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q7a"></A><H2>The link for my server / class / race is broken / not the best / missing. Can I suggest something?</H2>
<P>
Heck yes. You'll see most classes, races, servers etc have a link to another web site. For example, all the classes link to the Caster's Realm pages for their class. I've tried to link to places that I thought people would find useful. Most things have a link (not all) but if you have a comment or suggestion regarding these links then please <A HREF="mailto:lus@otn.co.uk">email me</A>.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q7c"></A><H2>How about letting me put all my characters stats and equipment into the system too?</H2>
<P>
This is something I specifically chose <B>not</B> to add. There are already a few systems out there that do this job very well such as <A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com">eq.castersrealm.com</A> and <A HREF="http://everquest.allakhazam.com">everquest.allakhazam.com</A>. Instead of reinventing that wheel I've included a field for each character called 'Character Website' where you can enter the link to your characters entry on one of those other sites.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>


<A NAME="q7d"></A><H2>Are there some images I can use to link from my site to GuildMagic?</H2>
<P>
<B>Yes!</B> Feel free to use the buttons below. In IE right click on the image and choose 'Save Picture As...' from the menu. In Netscape right click on the image and choose 'Save Image As...' from the menu.
<P>
