</CENTER>
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q8"></A><H2>How can I use GuildMagic to find other players in my timezone?</H2>
<P>
Click on the 'home' button on the left bar of the page. Click on the server you play on in the 'browse servers' box. Next you'll see a 'find character' section. In there you can choose your timezone from a drop-down box. Click 'search' to find other players on your server in your timezone.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q9"></A><H2>How can I use GuildMagic to find other players of a similar level?</H2>
<P>
Click on the 'home' button on the left bar of the page. Click on the server you play on in the 'browse servers' box. Next you'll see a 'find character' section. In there you can choose a minimum and maximum level from drop-down boxes.. Click 'search' to find other players on your server with the levels you specify.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q10"></A><H2>How can I use GuildMagic to find jeweler/blacksmith/etc on my server?</H2>
<P>
Click on the 'home' button on the left bar of the page. Click on the server you play on in the 'browse servers' box. Next you'll see a 'find character' section. In there you can choose the skill you need from a drop-down box. If you need someone with at least a certain skill score then you can also enter the miniumum value you need in the 'Min.Skill' box. Click 'search' to find players on your server with the skill you need..
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q11"></A><H2>I've forgotten my username or password. What do I do?</H2>
<P>
Go to the login page and click the link that says "I've forgotten my password". You will be taken to a page where you can enter your email address. When you do you will automaticaly be emailed with your username and password. Usernames and passwords will ONLY be emailed to the email address registered against the user. If you change your email address you must update your user details with GuildMagic. Otherwise you risk being unable to recover your username and password if you forget them.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q12"></A><H2>Why isn't my guild on the list of available guilds when I create a character?</H2>
<P>
Before you can put your characters into a guild you need to add your guild to your user. You do that by going to your 'my user' page and clicking 'add guilds to my user' in the 'guild memberships' section.
<P>
When you edit your character and put them into a guild you still need to have your guild leader accept that character into the guild. By setting the guild attribute of your character you automatically put a request on your guild leader's 'my user' page. The next time your guild leader logs in they will be able to accept or decline your request to have that character added to the guild.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q13"></A><H2>I've edited my character and selected that character's guild from the drop-down list but when I look at the guild roster my chracter isn't listed. What gives?</H2>
<P>
When you edit your character and put them into a guild you still need to have your guild leader accept that character into the guild. By setting the guild attribute of your character you automatically put a request on your guild leader's "my user" page. The next time your guild leader logs in they will be able to accept or decline your request to have that character added to the guild.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q14"></A><H2>Can I have characters on different servers?</H2>
<P>
Yes, you can make as many characters as you like under your user. Each character can be on a different server if you like.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q15"></A><H2>Can I have characters in different guilds?</H2>
<P>
Yes, you can make as many characters as you like under your user. Each character can be in a different guild if you like.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q16"></A><H2>Can I move my character betweens guilds?</H2>
<P>
Yes. Login and go to your 'my user' page (button in the left bar). Click the 'edit' button next to your character name. Now choose your new guild from the drop-down box where it says 'Guild'. If your required guild is not in that list then you need to give your Guildmagic username (not your character name) to the guild master. They will set you up so that you can see their guild on the list.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q17"></A><H2>How do I set skills for my character?</H2>
<P>
Login and go to your 'my user' page (button in the left bar). Click the 'skills' button next to your character. On the next page you'll see a list of available skills. Highlight the skill you want to add by clicking on it and then click the 'add skill' button below the box. You'll see a Skill section appear below for the skill you chose. You can set your ability score (1-250) and a description of your capabilities for each skill. When you're finished updating your skills click the 'finish' button at the bottom of the page.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q18"></A><H2>How do I link from my own web site to my character's page?</H2>
<P>
When you are logged in to GuildMagic and you view your character page (click 'view' next to your character on your 'my user' page) you'll see a short section at the bottom of the page telling you the HTML code you need to use. 
<P>
You could also just cut/paste the URL from your browser's address bar when you're viewing your character's page.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q19"></A><H2>How do I link from my own web site to my guild roster page?</H2>
<P>
When you are logged in to GuildMagic and you view your guild roster page (click 'view guild roster' next to your guild on your 'my user' page) you'll see a short section at the bottom of the page telling you the HTML code you need to use. 
<P>
You can change the sorting options on your guild roster page to the way you like them. When you've done that the HTML at the bottom of the page will make the link that you put on your own page come out sorted the way you left it.
<P>
You could also just cut/paste the URL from your browser's address bar when you have your guild roster page looking the way you like.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q19a"></A><H2>My server is splitting. How do I move my character to a new server?</H2>
<P>
Moving your character to a new server is as simple as editing your character (on your 'my user' page click 'edit' next to your character name). Next choose the name of the new server from the drop-down list titled 'Server'. 
<P>
Your guild administrator can move the guild to the new server independantly of this. Moving your character or guild to a new server will not remove you from the guild roster.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q19b"></A><H2>How come I can see all the details about this supposedly anonymous character here?</H2>
<P>
You can set your characters to be anonymous by editing them and clicking the <B>Character Anonymous</B> tickbox. This makes your character information hidden from everyone except your guild mates.
<P>
If you can see the details about a character that you know is set as anonymous then it must be because you have a character in the same guild as them.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q19b"></A><H2>Why can't I use find character to find a character I KNOW is in GuildMagic?</H2>
<P>
The character you're searching for is probably set as anonymous. Anonymous characters don't show up in Find Characters. This is because Find Characters can be used to look for certain races/classes/levels etc. Someone could find out all the information about an anonymous character that would normally be hidden by performing a series of searches.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q20"></A><H2>How do I create a guild?</H2>
<P>
Login and go to your 'my user' page. From there find the 'guild memberships' section and click the 'create new guild' button. You can set your guild name, guild web site and the server your new guild is on. These details can be edited later if they change. If your guild has branches on more than one server then you will need to make a separate guild for each server. It is possible to have two guilds with the same name on different servers.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q21"></A><H2>Can I be the administrator for more than one guild?</H2>
<P>
Yes, you can make as many guilds as you like under your user. Each guild you are administrator for will have a separate section on your 'my user' page.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q22"></A><H2>How do I allow my guild members to put their characters into my guild?</H2>
<P>
Before your guild members can try to add their characters to your guild you will need to get their GuildMagic usernames (not their character names) from them. When you have their username you should login and go to your 'my user' page. From there find the 'guild admin' section for your guild and enter their username in the box by the 'add user' button. Click the button and thay user can now start putting their characters in your guild. 
<P>
Before those characters will appear on your guild roster, though, you will need to accept or decline each character. As your guild members put their characters into your guild they will automatically generate a request that appears on your 'my user' page. Each request shows the username, character name and character details (level, race, class). You can accept or decline each character. When you are done you should click the 'edit characters' button in order to set each character with the correct 'role' (eg Trialist, Member, Leader etc). You can edit the roles list and make your own roles if you wish.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q22a"></A><H2>Some of my guild members have created their characters but haven't requested to have them added to the guild. How can add them?</H2>
<P>
If you a guild administrator you can invite your missing guild mates into your guild by clicking <B>recruit characters</B> on your admin controls. This takes you to a list of all the characters on your guild's server that aren't presently in a guild. Those that don't already have a request or invitation outstanding will have a <B>recruit</B> button next to their name. Click that button to invite them to join your guild. They will get an email inviting them to your guild. The email tells them that they should log into GuildMagic and click <B>accept</B> or <B>decline</B> next to the relevant character on their my user page. Once they've accepted or declined your invitation you will be sent an email explaining what they chose to do.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q22b"></A><H2>Can I stop my guild statistics from including information about the characters in my guild that are marked as Alternates?</H2>
<P>
Yes. If you are a guild administrator then you can choose whether alts are included in guild statistics by clicking on <B>edit guild info</B> on your admin controls. In there you'll find a tickbox called <B>Include alts in guild stats?</B>.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q23"></A><H2>How do I make one of my guild members into a guild administrator?</H2>
<P>
Guild administrators are made at a user level, not a character level. Login and go to your 'my user' page. Click the 'edit users' button on your 'guild admin' section. You'll see a list of all the users in your guild and below each one is a list of all the characters they have in your guild. If you click the 'edit' button next to one of those users you'll be able to set them as an administrator by ticking the 'Admin' box and clicking 'save'.
<P>
BEWARE! Do not give admin status to anyone that you do no trust implicitly. All guild  administrators have the same abilities in the GuildMagic system. Although you can never remove your own admin status, one of the other administrators CAN remove your admin status. 
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q24"></A><H2>How do I change the list of guild roles available?</H2>
<P>
Login and go to your 'my user' page. In the 'guild admin' section click the 'edit roles' button. You'll see a list of all the roles available to your guild. This list is in order with the most senior role at the top.
<P>
When your guild is created there are two roles created for you by default, 'Member' and 'Leader'. You can rename these roles and add new roles if you wish by clicking the 'edit' button next to a role or the 'add role' button. You can re-order the list using the up and down arrow buttons on the left.
<P>
When you are done click 'finished' at the bottom. Next you should click 'edit characters' back on your 'my user' page to make sure that your guild members are all set with the the correct roles.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q25"></A><H2>How do I change the role of one of my guild member's characters?</H2>
<P>
Login and go to your 'my user' page. Find the 'guild admin' section and click 'edit characters'. You'll see a list of all the characters in your guild. Click the 'edit' button next to the character you wish to change. You'll see a drop-down box appear with all the available roles. Choose the new role from the drop-down and click 'save' to save the change.
<P>
Click 'finished' at the bottom of the page when you are done.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q26"></A><H2>How do I remove a character (not user) from my guild?</H2>
<P>
Login and go to your 'my user' page. Find the 'guild admin' section and click 'edit characters'. You'll see a list of all the characters in your guild. Click the 'edit' button next to the character you wish to change. You'll see a drop-down box appear with all the available roles. At the bottom of that list is 'remove from guild'. Choose that and click 'save' to remove that character from the guild.
<P>
Click 'finished' at the bottom of the page when you are done.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q27"></A><H2>How do I remove a user (and all their characters) from my guild?</H2>
<P>
Login and go to your 'my user' page. Find the 'guild admin' section and click 'edit users'. You'll see a list of all the users and below each one is a list of all the characters they have in your guild. If you click the 'edit' button next to one of those users you'll see a button appear called 'remove guild access'. Click that button that user will no longer be able to add characters to your guild. In addition all of that user's characters that were in your guild will be removed from the guild.
<P>
Click 'finished' at the bottom of the page when you are done.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q28"></A><H2>How do I disband and delete my guild?</H2>
<P>
Login and go to your 'my user' page. Find the 'guild admin' section and click 'delete guild'. You will be asked to confirm what you are doing. This action cannot be undone. If you click OK then your guild will be deleted and all the characters in the guild will be removed from the guild.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q29"></A><H2>My server is splitting. How do I move my guild to a new server?</H2>
<P>
This will involve work on behalf of both you and your guild mates. Moving your guild to a new server is as easy as clicking 'edit guild info' on your guild administraton controls. You can choose your new server from the drop-down list of servers.
<P>
Once you've done that your guild will appear on the guild list for the new server and will still contain all the same characters it used to. All you need to do now is convince your guild members to edit their characters. <A HREF="#q19a">Click here</A> for information on how to move your character from one server to another.
<P>
<A HREF="#">back to top</A>
<P>

<A NAME="q30"></A><H2>One of my guild members has dinged but not updated their character entry. Can I update it for them?</H2>
<P>
Yes. On your admin controls click the <B>edit characters</B> button. On the next page find the character that you want to update and click <B>edit</B> next to that character. You will see that you can edit the character's level, guild role and main/alt status. Make your changes and click <B>save</B> to save the changes.
<P>
